{% extends 'extractors/_meta/extractor.j2' %}

{% block instructions %}
Read the source. Identify the **citations** for this source — list of citations; each is one of variants {paper|preprint, book, article, report} — see schema.

Use ONLY content the source supports. When the source is silent on a
field, set it to null (where the schema permits null). Never invent.

The schema enforces shape; load it implicitly via ``builders init`` and
fill the required fields below. Refer to the on-disk schema at
``templates/extractors/citations/schema.yaml`` for the exact field set,
required keys, and any per-variant rules.
{% endblock %}

{% block builder_calls %}

    curator.sh builders add {{ task.output_path }} \
        --set citations.<i>.<key>='<value>' [--set ...]

Repeat for each item / field group the schema requires. Indices are
0-based. For string|null fields, pass ``null`` to leave unset.
{% endblock %}
